<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-07T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-07T11:00:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 France/682: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in France (<persName corresp="#p_AN1" type="to">Armour</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-07T12:00:00-04:00">June
                                        7, 1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>213. British and Italian [representatives?] signed <persName corresp="#p_HH1">Hoover</persName> year debt postponement
                                agreement Saturday.<note n="43" xml:id="d404fn43">June 4.</note>
                                Treasury feels that it must within a very short time request French
                                payment due June 15th unless French agreement can be completed at
                                once.</p>
                            <p>Department assumes you are pressing this matter in every feasible
                                manner. Please report by wire.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>